WEBVTT

02:14.644 --> 02:15.812
Do you know
what time it is?

02:16.512 --> 02:17.645
Can't sleep.

02:17.647 --> 02:19.914
There are tabs
for that.

02:19.916 --> 02:21.718
Yeah, but then
I'd be sleeping.

02:22.352 --> 02:23.786
Dreams again?

02:28.324 --> 02:29.659
Wanna fight?

02:33.295 --> 02:34.428
I slipped.

02:34.430 --> 02:35.363
Right, you slipped

02:35.365 --> 02:37.365
as a result of me
punching you in the face.

02:37.367 --> 02:38.264
I was already slipping

02:38.266 --> 02:39.533
when you happened
to punch me in the face.

02:39.535 --> 02:41.136
The two events
were not related.

02:41.704 --> 02:42.705
Tell me about this dream.

02:45.541 --> 02:47.744
- Anything new?
- No.

02:52.214 --> 02:53.714
You have to let go
of the past.

02:53.716 --> 02:54.982
I don't remember my past.

02:54.984 --> 02:56.651
It's causing you doubt,

02:56.653 --> 02:58.454
and doubt
makes you vulnerable.

03:06.629 --> 03:07.664
Control it.

03:09.532 --> 03:11.532
Lose control again,
and you'll have to commune

03:11.534 --> 03:13.000
with the
Supreme Intelligence.

03:13.002 --> 03:15.872
There's nothing more dangerous
to a warrior than emotion.

03:18.975 --> 03:21.176
Humor is a distraction.

03:23.613 --> 03:25.379
And anger?

03:25.381 --> 03:26.816
Anger only serves
the enemy.

03:37.794 --> 03:39.660
<i>One hundred twenty days</i>

03:39.662 --> 03:41.696
<i>since the last Skrull attack.</i>

03:41.698 --> 03:43.030
<i>Has anyone ever seen</i>

03:43.032 --> 03:44.865
what the Supreme Intelligence
really looks like?

03:44.867 --> 03:47.635
No one can look upon
the Supreme Intelligence

03:47.637 --> 03:48.905
in its true form.

03:49.806 --> 03:52.006
You know that.

03:52.008 --> 03:54.742
Our subconscious chooses
the way they appear to us.

03:54.744 --> 03:58.278
So it's sacred.
It's personal.

03:58.280 --> 04:00.414
No Kree divulges it, ever.

04:00.416 --> 04:01.417
Who do you see?

04:02.452 --> 04:03.584
- Your brother?
- No.

04:03.586 --> 04:04.852
- Father?
- No.

04:04.854 --> 04:07.021
- Your old commander?
- Vers.

04:07.023 --> 04:08.424
It's me you see,
isn't it?

04:09.759 --> 04:11.425
I see
what you're trying to do.

04:11.427 --> 04:12.893
- Is it working?
- Yes.

04:12.895 --> 04:14.762
But you won't succeed
in changing the subject.

04:14.764 --> 04:17.364
What is the point
of giving me these...

04:17.366 --> 04:19.066
if you don't want me
to use them?

04:19.068 --> 04:20.935
I want you to use them.

04:20.937 --> 04:22.837
The Supreme Intelligence
gave me a responsibility...

04:22.839 --> 04:24.805
of showing you
how to use them.

04:24.807 --> 04:25.673
I know how.

04:25.675 --> 04:26.974
Yeah, if that were true,
you'd be able to

04:26.976 --> 04:27.977
knock me down without them.

04:29.612 --> 04:31.781
Control your impulses.

04:32.849 --> 04:35.916
Stop using this,
start using this.

04:35.918 --> 04:39.922
I want you to be
the best version of yourself.

05:20.963 --> 05:22.297
Vers.

05:23.065 --> 05:25.065
Intelligence.

05:25.067 --> 05:28.135
Your commander insists
that you're fit to serve.

05:28.137 --> 05:29.804
I am.

05:29.806 --> 05:33.407
You struggle
with your emotions...

05:33.409 --> 05:35.778
with your past,
which fuels them.

05:37.580 --> 05:40.714
You are just one victim
of the Skrull expansion...

05:40.716 --> 05:43.918
that has threatened our
civilization for centuries.

05:43.920 --> 05:46.987
Imposters
who silently infiltrate...

05:46.989 --> 05:48.991
then take over our planets.

05:50.827 --> 05:52.693
Horrors that you remember...

05:52.695 --> 05:55.331
and so much that you do not.

05:58.901 --> 06:02.736
It's all blank.
My life.

06:02.738 --> 06:04.438
You're supposed
to take the form

06:04.440 --> 06:06.106
of who I most admire...

06:06.108 --> 06:10.744
but I don't even remember
who this person was to me.

06:10.746 --> 06:12.813
Perhaps this is a mercy

06:12.815 --> 06:15.749
sparing you
from a deeper pain.

06:15.751 --> 06:19.653
Freeing you to do
what all Kree must...

06:19.655 --> 06:22.156
put your people's needs
before your own.

06:22.158 --> 06:24.692
We've given you
a great gift.

06:24.694 --> 06:27.129
The chance to fight
for the good of all Kree.

06:28.698 --> 06:29.964
I want to serve.

06:29.966 --> 06:32.032
Then master yourself.

06:32.034 --> 06:34.704
What was given
can be taken away.

06:39.008 --> 06:40.174
I won't let you down.

06:40.176 --> 06:42.411
We'll know soon enough.

06:42.912 --> 06:44.480
You have a mission.

06:45.815 --> 06:48.150
Serve well, and with honor.

07:09.105 --> 07:10.771
This can't be good.

07:10.773 --> 07:12.806
Must be another
Skrull attack.

07:12.808 --> 07:14.143
Whatever it is, it's big.

07:15.177 --> 07:16.677
Has a Skrull
ever simmed you?

07:16.679 --> 07:17.845
Once.

07:17.847 --> 07:20.214
- It was deeply disturbing.
- Why?

07:20.216 --> 07:22.616
Because I stared into the
face of my mortal enemy...

07:22.618 --> 07:24.852
and the face staring back
was my own.

07:24.854 --> 07:26.053
Maybe if you were
more attractive,

07:26.055 --> 07:27.688
then it would be
less disturbing.

07:27.690 --> 07:29.790
You think you're funny,
but I'm not laughing.

07:29.792 --> 07:31.025
You never laugh.

07:31.027 --> 07:34.094
I laugh on the inside.

07:34.096 --> 07:35.496
I'm not doing that now.

07:35.498 --> 07:36.664
It's funny 'cause,
objectively speaking,

07:36.666 --> 07:37.865
you're quite handsome.

07:37.867 --> 07:39.066
Well, thank you.

07:39.068 --> 07:41.669
Listen up, team.
Knock it off.

07:41.671 --> 07:42.705
All right.

07:43.272 --> 07:46.573
Prepare for...

07:46.575 --> 07:49.510
a search and rescue
of our spy, Soh-Larr.

07:49.512 --> 07:52.780
The Skrulls have invaded
yet another border planet.

07:52.782 --> 07:54.748
This time, Torfa.

07:54.750 --> 07:55.849
Soh-Larr sent us a warning.

07:55.851 --> 07:59.155
The signal was intercepted,
and his cover's blown.

08:00.990 --> 08:02.723
The Skrull general, Talos,

08:02.725 --> 08:04.591
has sent kill units
to find him.

08:04.593 --> 08:06.160
Should they reach him
before we do...

08:06.162 --> 08:07.561
the intelligence
he's acquired

08:07.563 --> 08:09.131
over three years
is as good as theirs.

08:10.633 --> 08:12.066
The Accusers will bomb

08:12.068 --> 08:14.168
a Skrull stronghold
here in the south.

08:14.170 --> 08:17.638
We slip in,
we locate Soh-Larr...

08:17.640 --> 08:20.774
and we get out,
leaving them none the wiser.

08:20.776 --> 08:23.043
The Torfan populace.

08:23.045 --> 08:24.545
We are not to interfere
with them,

08:24.547 --> 08:25.546
nor them with us.

08:25.548 --> 08:29.083
Nothing compromises
the security of our mission.

08:29.085 --> 08:31.085
Proceed with caution.

08:31.087 --> 08:33.255
Follow protocol
before extracting him.

08:34.991 --> 08:36.724
This is
a dangerous mission.

08:36.726 --> 08:39.660
We must all be ready
to join the Collective

08:39.662 --> 08:41.128
if that is our fate today.

08:41.130 --> 08:42.262
For the good of all Kree.

08:42.264 --> 08:43.265
For the good
of all Kree!

09:53.669 --> 09:56.203
Vers,
track Soh-Larr's beacon.

09:56.205 --> 09:58.908
Att-Lass, Minn-Erva,
find elevation.

10:17.893 --> 10:19.195
Locals on the periphery.

10:20.096 --> 10:21.695
Maybe a dozen.

10:21.697 --> 10:23.130
Minn-Erva?

10:24.667 --> 10:27.169
Do you read me?
Does anybody copy?

10:28.104 --> 10:29.169
Repeat.

10:42.918 --> 10:45.285
His beacon's coming from
that temple. Let's move.

10:45.287 --> 10:47.888
No. This is a perfect spot
for an ambush.

10:47.890 --> 10:49.123
Only one way in,
only one way out.

10:49.125 --> 10:50.858
We can get past the locals.

10:50.860 --> 10:53.461
We don't know if they are locals.
Too risky.

10:53.463 --> 10:54.862
You don't have to go
with me. I'll go alone.

10:54.864 --> 10:55.865
No, you won't.

11:00.870 --> 11:03.003
Right. We keep a close radius.

11:03.005 --> 11:05.040
We lose comms,
we meet back at the <i>Helion.</i>

11:06.108 --> 11:07.276
Come on.

11:19.456 --> 11:21.088
Att-Lass, you getting this?

11:21.090 --> 11:22.392
Copy. I see them.

11:32.502 --> 11:33.769
Get back!

11:34.337 --> 11:35.338
Commander?

11:42.978 --> 11:45.946
Get back! Back!

11:45.948 --> 11:48.717
Minn-Erva?
Do you have eyes on this?

11:49.818 --> 11:51.952
Keep them back.
Minn-Erva?

11:51.954 --> 11:53.756
Does anybody copy?

11:57.860 --> 11:59.128
I don't wanna hurt you.

12:01.897 --> 12:02.965
Keep back!

12:06.369 --> 12:07.370
Stay back!

12:11.508 --> 12:14.141
They're locals.
I found two dead. No green.

12:14.143 --> 12:15.844
They're just starving.

12:41.304 --> 12:43.036
HGX-78.

12:43.038 --> 12:45.841
TRT79-VVX6.

12:48.345 --> 12:50.246
Get back.

12:58.488 --> 12:59.489
Skrulls!

13:17.239 --> 13:18.373
Vers!

13:18.375 --> 13:20.575
<i>Vers? Skrulls.</i>

13:20.577 --> 13:22.445
<i>It's an ambush.</i>

13:41.431 --> 13:42.465
Incoming!

13:47.870 --> 13:49.470
Back to the <i>Helion.</i>

13:49.472 --> 13:50.806
<i>Vers. Do you copy?</i>

13:51.408 --> 13:53.408
<i>Back to the</i> Helion.

13:53.410 --> 13:54.642
<i>Come in. Vers.</i>

13:54.644 --> 13:57.177
How did you know the code?

13:57.179 --> 13:59.416
How about
I tell you my secret...

14:01.150 --> 14:03.453
when you've told me yours?

14:07.089 --> 14:08.491
<i>Let's open her up.</i>

14:20.670 --> 14:23.136
<i>Where are we?</i>

14:23.138 --> 14:24.474
<i>Stand by.</i>

14:26.343 --> 14:27.477
Where's your head at?

14:28.511 --> 14:31.011
In the clouds.
Where's yours?

14:31.013 --> 14:32.513
On my shoulders.

14:32.515 --> 14:34.349
About to show these boys
how we do it.

14:34.351 --> 14:35.916
You ready?

14:35.918 --> 14:36.983
Higher, further,
faster, baby.

14:36.985 --> 14:37.986
That's right.

14:47.963 --> 14:49.298
<i>This can't be right.</i>

14:50.999 --> 14:53.166
<i>Go back even further.</i>

14:56.406 --> 14:59.241
You're going too fast!
You need to go slow!

15:12.722 --> 15:15.390
<i>Who is this person?
Are we in the right...?</i>

15:15.392 --> 15:16.524
What the hell
are you thinking?

15:16.526 --> 15:17.558
You don't belong out here!

15:17.560 --> 15:19.259
<i>I think
we went back too far.</i>

15:19.261 --> 15:20.661
You let him drive.

15:20.663 --> 15:22.164
<i>Let me try something.</i>

15:24.467 --> 15:25.966
Give up already!

15:25.968 --> 15:27.470
You don't belong out here!

15:29.372 --> 15:32.205
You're not strong enough.

15:32.207 --> 15:33.476
You'll kill yourself.

15:39.349 --> 15:41.114
They'll never let you fly.

15:41.116 --> 15:43.518
<i>Am I the only one
that's confused here?</i>

15:43.520 --> 15:45.753
You're a decent pilot.

15:45.755 --> 15:46.788
But you're too emotional.

15:46.790 --> 15:50.056
You do know why they call it
a cockpit, don't you?

15:57.299 --> 16:00.568
A huge rumble throughout
the cosmos shook the moon...

16:00.570 --> 16:03.671
and the sun and the stars
in the sky.

16:03.673 --> 16:04.639
And so,

16:04.641 --> 16:07.274
little Alouette flew up
throughout the night.

16:07.276 --> 16:09.610
Did you see her?
It's Alouette.

16:11.046 --> 16:13.246
Get your butts inside,
it's time to eat.

16:13.248 --> 16:15.516
Prepare for takeoff,
Lieutenant Trouble.

16:15.518 --> 16:16.751
<i>Charming memory.</i>

16:16.753 --> 16:18.084
<i>Hang on.</i>

16:18.086 --> 16:19.389
<i>I think I've got it.</i>

16:24.159 --> 16:25.626
Goose likes you.

16:25.628 --> 16:27.260
She doesn't typically
take to people.

16:27.262 --> 16:28.663
Early start to your morning.

16:28.665 --> 16:30.096
Uh, late night, actually.

16:30.098 --> 16:32.165
I can't sleep
when there's work to do.

16:32.167 --> 16:33.099
Sound familiar?

16:33.101 --> 16:34.704
Flying your planes
never feels like work.

16:36.573 --> 16:37.805
Wonderful view, isn't it?

16:37.807 --> 16:40.040
I prefer the view
from up there.

16:40.042 --> 16:41.342
You'll get there
soon enough, Ace.

16:41.344 --> 16:43.478
<i>Wait! Wait, wait!
That's her. Get her back.</i>

16:43.480 --> 16:45.180
<i>Stand by.</i>

16:48.685 --> 16:50.217
Sound familiar?

16:50.219 --> 16:51.588
Wonderful view, isn't it?

16:53.790 --> 16:55.623
I prefer the view
from up there.

16:55.625 --> 16:57.057
You'll get there
soon enough, Ace.

16:57.059 --> 16:58.158
<i>What's that
on her shirt?</i>

16:58.160 --> 16:59.362
<i>I couldn't read it.</i>

17:00.797 --> 17:02.665
Wonderful view, isn't it?

17:05.401 --> 17:07.602
I prefer the view
from up there.

17:07.604 --> 17:10.203
- <i>Focus.</i>
- Excuse me?

17:10.205 --> 17:12.072
<i>Look down.</i>

17:12.074 --> 17:14.107
<i>Focus.</i>

17:14.109 --> 17:16.777
<i>"Pegasus. Dr. Wendy Lawson."
That's her.</i>

17:16.779 --> 17:17.745
Do you hear that, too?

17:17.747 --> 17:19.382
<i>Do we have
her location?</i>

17:21.484 --> 17:23.049
<i>Got it.</i>

17:23.051 --> 17:25.455
<i>Now track Lawson until
we find the energy signature.</i>

17:29.726 --> 17:31.394
<i>Interesting.</i>

17:32.829 --> 17:35.496
<i>Huh. Hold on.</i>

17:35.498 --> 17:38.301
<i>Go back right before this.
Go back.</i>

17:40.403 --> 17:41.869
That's no MiG, Lawson.

17:41.871 --> 17:44.505
<i>This is it.
Now let me see where you're headed.</i>

17:44.507 --> 17:46.676
<i>That's right.
Look at the coordinates.</i>

17:47.410 --> 17:48.745
<i>Focus.</i>

17:50.547 --> 17:52.380
<i>Open, please.</i>

17:52.382 --> 17:53.748
<i>That's it. That's it.</i>

17:53.750 --> 17:54.815
<i>You're almost there.</i>

17:54.817 --> 17:56.686
<i>You're almost there.
Don't fight it.</i>

17:58.421 --> 17:59.622
<i>Focus!</i>

18:01.491 --> 18:03.125
<i>Get her back!
Get her back now!</i>

18:07.730 --> 18:09.195
This doesn't make any sense.

18:24.246 --> 18:28.416
Do we have any information
we can act on?

18:28.418 --> 18:31.217
Just that Lawson was
somewhere on planet C-53.

18:31.219 --> 18:32.353
We're on our way.

18:32.355 --> 18:35.221
Then dig, dig, dig deeper.

18:35.223 --> 18:38.394
Lawson is our link
to that light-speed engine!

18:39.629 --> 18:41.096
And everything we're after.

18:48.671 --> 18:49.672
Oh!

18:50.640 --> 18:51.939
That did something.

18:51.941 --> 18:53.376
Try that again.

19:04.887 --> 19:05.888
Not yet!

19:15.531 --> 19:17.632
What did you do to me?

19:17.634 --> 19:19.600
Now we're just after
a little information.

19:19.602 --> 19:21.302
What did you put in my head?

19:21.304 --> 19:23.205
Nothing that wasn't
already there.

19:24.741 --> 19:26.307
But those aren't my memories.

19:26.309 --> 19:28.843
Yeah, it's like a bad trip,
isn't it?

19:28.845 --> 19:31.345
I'm not surprised
you can't keep it straight.

19:31.347 --> 19:33.547
They really did
a number on you.

19:33.549 --> 19:34.715
Enough of your mind games.

19:34.717 --> 19:36.617
What do you want?

19:38.388 --> 19:40.888
We're looking for the location
of a Dr. Lawson...

19:40.890 --> 19:42.657
and her light-speed engine.

19:42.659 --> 19:44.525
I don't know any Dr. Lawson.

19:44.527 --> 19:48.163
Really? Then why is she
in your head?

20:18.961 --> 20:20.260
You guys
wouldn't happen to know

20:20.262 --> 20:21.263
how these things come off,
would ya?

20:21.764 --> 20:22.897
No?

20:22.899 --> 20:24.299
Fine.

20:46.989 --> 20:47.990
Hmm.

21:55.958 --> 21:56.959
Hey.

22:02.398 --> 22:03.633
<i>You do
know why they call it a...</i>

22:21.651 --> 22:23.884
You leaving so soon?

22:23.886 --> 22:25.421
We're just getting to know
each other.

23:48.804 --> 23:51.807
Vers to Starforce command,
do you read me?

23:54.076 --> 23:56.679
Hello? Do you copy?

24:26.108 --> 24:28.108
Hi. I'm Vers.
Kree Starforce.

24:28.110 --> 24:29.445
Is this C-53?

24:31.914 --> 24:34.682
Do you understand me? Is my
universal translator working?

24:34.684 --> 24:36.951
Yeah. I understand you.

24:36.953 --> 24:38.018
Oh, good.

24:38.020 --> 24:40.056
Are you in charge of security
for this district?

24:41.857 --> 24:44.727
Sort of. Uh,
the movie theater has its own guy.

24:46.095 --> 24:47.997
Where can I find
communications equipment?

24:55.104 --> 24:56.205
Thank you.

25:29.205 --> 25:31.240
Track the pod.
Find the girl.

25:32.274 --> 25:34.877
She knows more
than she knows.

25:37.146 --> 25:38.214
Hey.

25:39.582 --> 25:40.916
This one's taken.

25:51.594 --> 25:53.193
Come on.

25:53.195 --> 25:54.362
<i>Vers?</i>

25:54.364 --> 25:55.631
Vers?

25:56.298 --> 25:58.299
Verify. CTC-39.

25:58.301 --> 25:59.767
<i>GRXV-1600.</i>

25:59.769 --> 26:00.936
<i>And I'm fine,
thank you for asking.</i>

26:02.038 --> 26:03.670
<i>Is everyone okay?
What happened?</i>

26:03.672 --> 26:05.639
Skrull ambush.

26:05.641 --> 26:07.241
I thought we'd lost you.

26:07.243 --> 26:08.376
Did you find Soh-Larr?

26:08.378 --> 26:09.877
<i>It wasn't Soh-Larr.</i>

26:09.879 --> 26:11.945
<i>Talos simmed him.
Even knew his code.</i>

26:11.947 --> 26:14.181
That's impossible.

26:14.183 --> 26:16.183
That code was buried
in his unconscious.

26:16.185 --> 26:17.751
The Skrulls
messed with my mind.

26:17.753 --> 26:18.852
The machine that they used...

26:18.854 --> 26:21.255
I think it's how they
extracted Soh-Larr's code.

26:21.257 --> 26:22.390
Vers, where are you?

26:22.392 --> 26:24.792
<i>I'm on planet C-53.</i>

26:24.794 --> 26:27.194
The Skrulls are looking for
someone named Lawson.

26:27.196 --> 26:28.796
<i>Who?</i>

26:28.798 --> 26:32.032
She's who I see.

26:32.034 --> 26:33.736
<i>She's what?</i>

26:34.304 --> 26:35.738
<i>Vers?</i>

26:36.806 --> 26:37.807
Vers, what?

26:39.141 --> 26:40.408
She's a scientist.

26:40.410 --> 26:42.643
They think that she's cracked
the code on light-speed tech.

26:42.645 --> 26:44.244
I have to get to her
before they do...

26:44.246 --> 26:45.946
<i>or else they'll be able
to invade new galaxies.</i>

26:45.948 --> 26:47.750
No. You've been
caught once already.

26:48.951 --> 26:51.118
How far is C-53?

26:51.120 --> 26:53.821
Closest jump point
is 22 hours.

26:53.823 --> 26:55.956
<i>Vers, hold your
position until we get there.</i>

26:55.958 --> 26:58.025
<i>Keep your comms online
so we can contact you.</i>

26:58.027 --> 26:59.993
No! What if they get
a hold of it before...

26:59.995 --> 27:01.095
<i>We're sorry.</i>

27:01.097 --> 27:02.262
<i>A long-distance
company access code</i>

27:02.264 --> 27:02.763
<i>is required for the number
you have dialed.</i>

27:02.765 --> 27:04.967
- Yon-Rogg?
- Vers?

27:06.303 --> 27:07.502
Vers?

27:07.504 --> 27:09.002
<i>Please dial your call
with the access code.</i>

27:09.004 --> 27:11.105
Vers?

27:11.107 --> 27:13.941
If the Skrulls got
to her, she's compromised.

27:13.943 --> 27:15.945
She's stronger
than you think.

27:16.812 --> 27:18.781
Ever been to C-53?

27:19.316 --> 27:20.383
Once.

27:21.217 --> 27:23.351
It's a real shithole.

27:33.896 --> 27:36.799
Hey, rookie!
Go talk to the rent-a-cop.

27:43.873 --> 27:45.308
Did you call this in?

28:00.055 --> 28:01.056
<i>Beacon activated.</i>

28:04.427 --> 28:06.026
Excuse me, miss.

28:06.028 --> 28:08.463
You know anything
about a lady blowing a hole...

28:08.465 --> 28:11.932
through the roof of that
Blockbuster over there?

28:11.934 --> 28:14.437
Witness says
she was dressed for laser tag.

28:15.938 --> 28:17.338
Oh.

28:17.340 --> 28:20.007
Yeah, I think
she went that way.

28:20.009 --> 28:23.344
Uh, I'd like to ask you
some questions.

28:23.346 --> 28:27.848
Maybe give you the 411
on the late-night drop box.

28:27.850 --> 28:29.850
Could I see
some identification, please?

28:29.852 --> 28:31.352
Vers. Kree Starforce.

28:31.354 --> 28:32.453
We don't carry
our identification

28:32.455 --> 28:33.521
on little cards.

28:33.523 --> 28:34.723
Vers?

28:35.392 --> 28:37.226
Starforce?

28:38.761 --> 28:40.194
How long you plan
to be in town?

28:40.196 --> 28:41.362
oh, I'll be
out of your hair...

28:41.364 --> 28:42.829
as soon as I track down
the Skrulls

28:42.831 --> 28:44.401
that are infiltrating
your planet.

28:45.435 --> 28:46.769
Skrulls?

28:47.169 --> 28:48.336
Shapeshifters?

28:48.338 --> 28:51.408
They can transform into any
life-form down to the DNA.

28:52.975 --> 28:55.075
Oh, boy. You guys don't have
any clue, do you?

28:55.077 --> 28:57.978
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hold on.

28:57.980 --> 29:03.351
How do we know you're not
one of those shapeshifters?

29:03.353 --> 29:05.320
Congratulations, Agent Fury.

29:05.322 --> 29:07.388
You have finally asked
a relevant question.

29:07.390 --> 29:10.491
No! Congratulations to you,
Starforce lady.

29:10.493 --> 29:12.761
You're under arrest.

29:20.437 --> 29:21.804
Rook!

29:22.505 --> 29:23.906
Rook, let's roll!

29:33.483 --> 29:34.915
Did you see her weapon?

29:34.917 --> 29:36.016
I did not.

29:45.961 --> 29:47.062
Watch it!

30:19.562 --> 30:22.097
Suspect on northbound train.
In pursuit.

30:43.152 --> 30:45.954
"Trust me,
true believer." "Trust me."

30:50.893 --> 30:53.095
"Trust me, true believer."

31:39.208 --> 31:40.209
Get off!

32:35.998 --> 32:37.600
Train's heading
for a tunnel up ahead.

32:40.637 --> 32:42.605
Let's greet them
at the station.

32:54.249 --> 32:56.251
<i>Mr. Fury,
this is Agent Coulson.</i>

32:57.353 --> 32:59.288
Uh, I'm still here
at the Blockbuster.

33:01.458 --> 33:03.156
And, uh,
where'd everybody go?

33:03.158 --> 33:05.160
<i>I finished
collecting evidence...</i>

34:33.383 --> 34:34.715
We need an ambulance!

34:34.717 --> 34:36.182
Someone call 911!

34:36.184 --> 34:37.718
Hey! You all right?

34:37.720 --> 34:39.720
Oh, my gosh!
Is everyone okay?

34:39.722 --> 34:40.688
Anyone else see that?

34:40.690 --> 34:44.425
Official S.H.I.E.L.D.
activity. Stay back.

35:32.575 --> 35:34.609
Nice scuba suit.

35:39.716 --> 35:41.716
Lighten up, honey, huh?

35:41.718 --> 35:43.586
Got a smile for me?

35:47.790 --> 35:49.124
Freak.

36:08.444 --> 36:12.278
All life on Earth
is carbon-based. Not this guy.

36:12.280 --> 36:14.649
Whatever he runs on,

36:14.651 --> 36:16.216
it's not
on the periodic table.

36:16.218 --> 36:18.688
You're saying
he's not from around here?

36:19.689 --> 36:20.757
Hey, how's your eye?

36:21.758 --> 36:24.257
Well, I'd say fine...

36:24.259 --> 36:26.562
but it can't believe
what it's seeing.

36:29.264 --> 36:34.402
You say this thing
looked like Coulson?

36:34.404 --> 36:36.437
Mmm. Talked like him, too.

36:36.439 --> 36:39.340
And the woman said
that there were more?

36:39.342 --> 36:41.409
The word she used
was "infiltration."

36:41.411 --> 36:42.576
You believe her?

36:42.578 --> 36:44.879
Not till I saw this.

36:44.881 --> 36:47.948
What's your plan?

36:47.950 --> 36:49.917
I'll find Blockbuster girl.

36:49.919 --> 36:52.319
I got word
on a motorcycle thief

36:52.321 --> 36:54.254
that fits her description.

36:54.256 --> 36:56.991
If she can tell us
why these lizards are here...

36:56.993 --> 36:59.427
maybe she can tell us
how to kick 'em to the curb.

36:59.429 --> 37:00.430
Good.

37:01.698 --> 37:04.266
Do it alone, though.
We can't trust anyone.

37:05.368 --> 37:07.501
Not even our own men.

37:07.503 --> 37:08.705
Yes, sir.

37:23.052 --> 37:26.353
Wow. They're ugly bastards,
aren't they?

37:26.355 --> 37:29.859
Yeah,
well, he's no Brad Pitt, sir.

37:34.731 --> 37:37.299
Safe journey to the beyond,
my friend.

37:39.035 --> 37:41.971
I will finish
what we started.

37:50.646 --> 37:52.648
I wouldn't get
too close there, boss.

37:54.650 --> 37:56.419
No one in or out.

38:32.021 --> 38:33.354
Boom!

38:58.548 --> 38:59.980
What can I get ya?

38:59.982 --> 39:01.551
Where was
this photograph taken?

39:02.518 --> 39:03.717
An airport.

39:03.719 --> 39:05.052
Where's Pegasus?

39:05.054 --> 39:07.121
That's classified.

39:07.123 --> 39:10.493
Not unlike the file
I started on you.

39:12.528 --> 39:14.795
But I see you've changed
it up a bit since then.

39:14.797 --> 39:16.630
Grunge is a good look
for you.

39:16.632 --> 39:18.165
Did you have a rough day,
Agent Fury?

39:18.167 --> 39:19.867
It was cool, you know?

39:19.869 --> 39:22.837
Had a space invasion,
big car chase.

39:22.839 --> 39:26.874
Got to watch
an alien autopsy.

39:26.876 --> 39:28.609
Typical nine-to-five.

39:28.611 --> 39:29.543
So you saw one?

39:29.545 --> 39:32.515
I was never one
to believe in aliens...

39:33.482 --> 39:35.716
but I can't unsee that.

39:35.718 --> 39:38.419
This is gonna get a little
awkward, but I gotta ask.

39:38.421 --> 39:40.788
You think I'm one of
those green things.

39:40.790 --> 39:42.156
Can't be too careful.

39:42.158 --> 39:47.127
You are looking at
100% red-blooded Earth man.

39:47.129 --> 39:48.662
I'm afraid
I'm gonna need proof.

39:48.664 --> 39:50.764
We talking cheek swab
or urine sample?

39:50.766 --> 39:52.700
No. The DNA would match.

39:52.702 --> 39:53.901
Want my AOL password?

39:53.903 --> 39:55.936
Skrulls can only sim
recent memories

39:55.938 --> 39:57.940
- of their host bodies.
- Oh, oh.

39:59.108 --> 40:01.041
You wanna get personal.

40:01.043 --> 40:02.943
- Where were you born?
- Huntsville, Alabama.

40:02.945 --> 40:04.578
But technically,
I don't remember that part.

40:04.580 --> 40:06.046
- Name of your first pet?
- Mr. Snoofers.

40:06.048 --> 40:07.548
- Mr. Snoofers?
- That's what I said.

40:07.550 --> 40:08.616
Do I pass?

40:08.618 --> 40:10.017
Not yet. First job?

40:10.019 --> 40:11.886
Soldier. Straight out of
high school.

40:11.888 --> 40:13.153
Left the ranks
a full bird colonel.

40:13.155 --> 40:14.521
- Then?
- Spy.

40:14.523 --> 40:15.656
- Where?
- It was the Cold War.

40:15.658 --> 40:16.891
We were everywhere.

40:16.893 --> 40:19.760
Uh, Belfast. Bucharest.
Belgrade. Budapest.

40:19.762 --> 40:21.495
I like the B's.
I can make them rhyme.

40:21.497 --> 40:22.663
- Now?
- Been riding a desk

40:22.665 --> 40:23.764
for the past six years...

40:23.766 --> 40:24.865
trying to figure out
where our

40:24.867 --> 40:25.933
future enemies
are coming from.

40:25.935 --> 40:27.134
Never occurred to me

40:27.136 --> 40:29.670
they would be coming
from above.

40:29.672 --> 40:31.005
Name a detail so bizarre

40:31.007 --> 40:32.441
a Skrull could never
fabricate it.

40:34.777 --> 40:38.514
If toast is cut diagonally,
I can't eat it.

40:40.249 --> 40:41.949
You didn't need that,
did you?

40:41.951 --> 40:43.686
No. No, I didn't.
But I enjoyed it.

40:44.186 --> 40:46.020
Okay. Your turn.

40:46.022 --> 40:47.757
Prove you're not a Skrull.

40:56.232 --> 40:58.933
And how is that
supposed to prove to me

40:58.935 --> 41:00.234
you're not a Skrull?

41:00.236 --> 41:01.637
That's a photon blast.

41:01.871 --> 41:03.070
And?

41:03.072 --> 41:04.073
A Skrull can't do that.

41:05.174 --> 41:06.540
So, a full bird colonel

41:06.542 --> 41:07.808
turned spy
turned S.H.I.E.L.D. agent...

41:07.810 --> 41:10.179
must have pretty high
security clearance.

41:10.813 --> 41:11.881
Where's Pegasus?

41:17.620 --> 41:20.621
Okay.
The Skrulls sim alien races

41:20.623 --> 41:22.556
to infiltrate
and take over planets.

41:22.558 --> 41:26.727
And you're a Kree?
A race of noble warriors?

41:26.729 --> 41:29.263
Heroes.
Noble warrior heroes.

41:29.265 --> 41:32.935
So, um, what do Skrulls
want with Dr. Lawson?

41:34.170 --> 41:36.103
They believe
that she developed

41:36.105 --> 41:38.105
a light-speed engine
at Pegasus.

41:38.107 --> 41:39.742
Light-speed engine?

41:40.810 --> 41:42.142
Gotta admit, that's not

41:42.144 --> 41:43.711
the craziest thing
I've heard today.

41:43.713 --> 41:45.313
Well, it's still early.

41:45.315 --> 41:47.581
And you,
what do you want?

41:47.583 --> 41:49.883
To stop the Skrulls before
they become unstoppable.

41:49.885 --> 41:50.886
And?

41:55.024 --> 41:58.592
Look, war is
a universal language.

41:58.594 --> 42:01.295
I know a rogue soldier
when I see one.

42:01.297 --> 42:03.699
You got a personal stake
in this.

42:13.809 --> 42:15.609
<i>This is government property.</i>

42:15.611 --> 42:17.611
<i>Turn your vehicle around.</i>

42:17.613 --> 42:20.781
Nicholas Joseph Fury.
Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.

42:20.783 --> 42:22.918
<i>Place your thumb on the pad.</i>

42:24.020 --> 42:25.853
<i>One moment.</i>

42:25.855 --> 42:29.990
Nicholas Joseph Fury.
You have three names?

42:29.992 --> 42:31.725
Everybody calls me Fury.

42:31.727 --> 42:35.763
Not Nicholas. Not Joseph.
Not Nick. Just Fury.

42:35.765 --> 42:37.231
- What does your mom call you?
- Fury.

42:37.233 --> 42:38.966
- What do you call her?
- Fury.

42:38.968 --> 42:40.134
What about your kids?

42:40.136 --> 42:42.069
If I have them,
they'll call me Fury.

42:42.071 --> 42:43.304
<i>You are cleared
for access.</i>

42:43.306 --> 42:44.307
Thank you.

43:14.337 --> 43:16.136
Oh, hold up.

43:16.138 --> 43:18.874
You look like somebody's
disaffected niece.

43:20.876 --> 43:21.877
Put that on.

43:23.313 --> 43:25.346
- What is it?
- It's the S.H.I.E.L.D. logo.

43:25.348 --> 43:28.148
Does, uh, announcing
your identity on clothing

43:28.150 --> 43:29.883
help with the covert part
of your job?

43:29.885 --> 43:32.088
Said the space soldier who
was wearing a rubber suit.

43:33.155 --> 43:34.290
Lose the flannel.

43:45.368 --> 43:47.402
How can I help you?

43:47.404 --> 43:49.605
We're agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.

43:51.941 --> 43:54.041
We're looking for a woman
named Lawson.

43:54.043 --> 43:56.245
A Dr. Wendy Lawson.

43:57.880 --> 43:59.281
Do you know her?

44:03.719 --> 44:04.920
Follow me.

44:05.422 --> 44:06.622
Hmm.

44:09.225 --> 44:12.628
You familiar with the phrase
"welcome wagon"?

44:13.430 --> 44:14.630
No.

44:15.865 --> 44:18.100
Well, this ain't it.

44:25.342 --> 44:26.740
Is that a communicator?

44:26.742 --> 44:30.110
Yeah. State-of-the-art
two-way pager.

44:30.112 --> 44:31.312
Who are you paging?

44:31.314 --> 44:35.050
My mom. Don't worry.
I didn't mention you.

45:13.756 --> 45:14.888
After you.

45:14.890 --> 45:16.524
Impressive.

45:16.526 --> 45:19.295
Oh, you should see what I
can do with a paperclip.

45:30.005 --> 45:32.274
Hey, there. How are you?

45:34.143 --> 45:37.144
Oh, my goodness. Look at you.
Just look at you.

45:37.146 --> 45:39.780
Aren't you
the cutest little thing?

45:39.782 --> 45:42.015
Aren't you cute?
And what's your name, huh?

45:42.017 --> 45:43.150
What's your name?

45:43.152 --> 45:46.053
"Goose."
Cool name for a cool cat.

45:46.055 --> 45:47.056
Fury?

45:47.324 --> 45:48.325
Hmm?

45:50.460 --> 45:51.894
I'll be back.

45:55.164 --> 45:57.432
Oh! Let me get
my fingerprint out.

45:57.434 --> 45:59.001
Just let me unravel
this puppy.

46:03.239 --> 46:05.806
You sat there and watched me
play with tape?

46:05.808 --> 46:06.940
When all you had to do was...

46:06.942 --> 46:08.345
I didn't wanna steal
your thunder.

46:25.428 --> 46:27.497
Huh. Lawson.

46:37.507 --> 46:40.843
Lawson's plan
for the light-speed engine.

46:42.111 --> 46:44.278
I wonder why
they terminated the project.

46:44.280 --> 46:48.784
Um, maybe because
she's cuckoo.

46:51.253 --> 46:52.389
Kree glyphs?

46:52.955 --> 46:54.023
Hmm?

46:55.291 --> 46:56.992
Lawson is not cuckoo.

46:59.261 --> 47:01.094
She's Kree.

47:01.096 --> 47:03.598
Well, she's dead.

47:03.600 --> 47:05.265
What?

47:05.267 --> 47:07.067
She crashed
the Asis aircraft

47:07.069 --> 47:09.136
doing an unauthorized
test flight.

47:09.138 --> 47:11.238
Took a pilot down
with her.

47:11.240 --> 47:13.508
That's why security here
is so unfriendly.

47:13.510 --> 47:16.546
They're covering up
a billion-dollar mistake.

47:18.213 --> 47:20.983
Oh, and your light-speed
engine is toast.

47:24.421 --> 47:26.021
When did this crash happen?

47:26.656 --> 47:29.892
Six years ago. 1989.

47:31.026 --> 47:33.226
Who was the pilot?

47:33.228 --> 47:36.497
Um, most of
this thing's redacted...

47:36.499 --> 47:40.967
but there is a testimonial
here from a Maria Rambeau.

47:40.969 --> 47:43.005
Last person
to see them alive.

47:48.277 --> 47:49.412
You okay?

47:51.246 --> 47:52.382
Mm-hmm.

47:54.049 --> 47:55.284
Back in a minute.

48:25.348 --> 48:27.582
This isn't about
fighting wars.

48:27.584 --> 48:29.184
It's about ending them.

48:35.257 --> 48:36.990
<i>I know Lawson was Kree.</i>

48:36.992 --> 48:40.060
She was here on C-53
and died in a plane crash.

48:40.062 --> 48:42.697
<i>Do you know anything
about this?</i>

48:42.699 --> 48:44.432
I just discovered
a mission report

48:44.434 --> 48:46.266
sent from C-53.

48:46.268 --> 48:47.368
There's only so much

48:47.370 --> 48:50.072
I'm cleared to tell you,
Vers, but...

48:53.676 --> 48:58.078
<i>Lawson was an undercover
Kree operative named Mar-Vell.</i>

48:58.080 --> 49:01.682
She was working
on a unique energy core.

49:01.684 --> 49:03.183
Experimenting with tech

49:03.185 --> 49:06.054
that apparently could
help us win the war.

49:12.729 --> 49:14.194
She still here?

49:14.196 --> 49:16.697
She's cooperating
with the investigation, sir.

49:16.699 --> 49:18.733
- You men stay here.
- Yes, sir.

49:18.735 --> 49:20.703
I want to
question her alone.

49:22.439 --> 49:24.674
Excellent work, Nicholas.

49:28.445 --> 49:30.445
Does it say anything
about me?

49:30.447 --> 49:32.313
Anything about you?
No, of course not.

49:32.315 --> 49:33.246
<i>Why would it?</i>

49:33.248 --> 49:36.684
I found evidence
that I had a life here.

49:36.686 --> 49:38.388
<i>On C-53?</i>

49:40.723 --> 49:42.289
Mar-Vell is who I see

49:42.291 --> 49:43.724
when I visit
the Supreme Intelligence.

49:43.726 --> 49:47.194
I knew her.
And I knew her as Lawson.

49:47.196 --> 49:49.530
This sounds like
Skrull simulation, Vers.

49:49.532 --> 49:51.499
No, it's not. Because I remember.
I was here.

49:51.501 --> 49:53.434
<i>Stop. Remember your training.</i>

49:53.436 --> 49:55.770
Know your enemy.
It could be you.

49:55.772 --> 49:59.241
<i>Do not let your emotions
override your judgment.</i>

50:00.610 --> 50:02.510
She's on sublevel six.

50:02.512 --> 50:04.144
I'll get off on five...

50:04.146 --> 50:07.315
and take the stairs in case
she makes a run for it.

50:07.317 --> 50:10.451
Do a pincer move
like we did in Havana.

50:10.453 --> 50:13.423
Right. Like we did
in Havana.

50:24.266 --> 50:25.366
<i>We're nearing
the jump point.</i>

50:25.368 --> 50:27.735
<i>Leave your beacon on
so I can find you.</i>

50:27.737 --> 50:30.304
We'll get to
the bottom of this, Vers.

50:30.306 --> 50:32.007
Together.

50:34.444 --> 50:35.712
Okay.

50:53.463 --> 50:55.063
Vers!

50:56.633 --> 50:58.033
Vers!

51:14.717 --> 51:16.551
Fury's colluding
with the target.

51:16.553 --> 51:17.885
Then why would he call us in?

51:17.887 --> 51:19.453
All I know is
we take him in, too.

51:19.455 --> 51:20.588
Dead or alive.

51:20.590 --> 51:21.889
Dead or alive?

51:36.706 --> 51:37.941
Go. Go, go!

51:50.520 --> 51:52.622
Was it something I said?

52:10.640 --> 52:11.674
Mmm-mmm.

52:31.361 --> 52:35.763
Now, you know, I don't really
need these to see...

52:35.765 --> 52:39.769
but they do
kinda complete the look.

52:40.503 --> 52:41.704
Don't you think?

52:59.355 --> 53:00.488
You called them in?

53:00.490 --> 53:01.824
My bad.

53:16.339 --> 53:18.005
Coulson,
do you have eyes on them?

53:18.007 --> 53:19.742
They're not down here.

53:21.276 --> 53:22.311
Let's try up there.

53:31.521 --> 53:32.853
- What?
- Your communicator.

53:32.855 --> 53:34.922
You obviously
can't be trusted with it.

54:05.588 --> 54:07.421
Do you know
how to fly this thing?

54:07.423 --> 54:08.556
Uh, we'll see.

54:08.558 --> 54:09.959
That's a yes or no question.

54:13.996 --> 54:14.997
Yes.

54:18.735 --> 54:20.268
That's what I'm talking about!

54:47.530 --> 54:48.731
We got a stowaway.

54:52.835 --> 54:53.903
Hang on, Goose.

54:59.075 --> 55:00.275
Goose.

55:03.446 --> 55:04.447
No, Goose.

55:05.782 --> 55:09.416
Who's a good kitty, huh?
Huh, Goose?

55:09.418 --> 55:11.085
Yes, that's right.

55:11.087 --> 55:13.454
Who's a good kitty, Goose?

55:13.456 --> 55:14.755
You the good kitty,
that's right.

55:14.757 --> 55:15.892
See anyone you know?

55:17.760 --> 55:19.426
Funny story.

55:19.428 --> 55:22.965
I arrived on Hala near dead.
No memory.

55:23.833 --> 55:25.065
That was six years ago.

55:25.067 --> 55:27.468
So, you think
you're the pilot

55:27.470 --> 55:28.803
that went down
with Dr. Lawson?

55:28.805 --> 55:31.138
I'm saying the last person
to see them alive

55:31.140 --> 55:32.473
could probably tell us.

55:32.475 --> 55:34.074
- Maria Rambeau?
- Mm-hmm.

55:34.076 --> 55:36.777
So, how do we get
to Louisiana?

55:36.779 --> 55:39.448
Due east.
Hang a right at Memphis.

55:40.883 --> 55:42.917
That agent...

55:42.919 --> 55:44.985
that stopped the Skrulls
from finding us?

55:44.987 --> 55:47.054
Coulson. The new guy.

55:47.056 --> 55:48.656
I guess
he doesn't hate me yet.

55:48.658 --> 55:50.393
Yeah, well, give him time.

55:52.395 --> 55:54.061
I guess he had a feeling,
you know?

55:54.063 --> 55:56.497
Went with his gut
against orders.

55:56.499 --> 55:57.932
That's a really
hard thing to do.

55:57.934 --> 55:59.967
But it's what
keeps us human.

55:59.969 --> 56:02.603
I get in trouble for that.
A lot.

56:02.605 --> 56:03.737
Oh, I can see that about you.

56:04.874 --> 56:09.043
Rescuing the guy who sold
you out to the Skrulls?

56:09.045 --> 56:10.477
I'm guessing that's not

56:10.479 --> 56:12.112
standard
Kree operating procedure.

56:12.114 --> 56:14.481
Well, I won't tell your boss
if you don't tell mine.

56:22.625 --> 56:23.757
Ronan.

56:23.759 --> 56:25.793
<i>The Accusers completed
their operation...</i>

56:25.795 --> 56:27.194
<i>but the greater mission
was a failure,</i>

56:27.196 --> 56:28.596
<i>thanks to your team.</i>

56:28.598 --> 56:30.064
It was a trap

56:30.066 --> 56:32.900
to lure our operative Vers
to Torfa and kidnap her.

56:32.902 --> 56:34.034
<i>Give us their location.</i>

56:34.036 --> 56:35.903
<i>We'll take care
of the terrorist threat.</i>

56:35.905 --> 56:38.839
By bombing them
out of the galaxy?

56:38.841 --> 56:41.041
No, we'll handle this.

56:41.043 --> 56:43.143
<i>A cell of Skrulls anywhere</i>

56:43.145 --> 56:45.479
<i>is a threat
to Kree everywhere.</i>

56:45.481 --> 56:46.547
<i>Where are they?</i>

56:46.549 --> 56:48.117
- They are...
- Lost.

56:49.452 --> 56:51.919
They are lost for now.

56:51.921 --> 56:53.654
But we will find them.

56:53.656 --> 56:57.026
<i>Do so, or we will.</i>

57:01.130 --> 57:03.666
Maintain the course
for C-53.

57:22.885 --> 57:25.054
Excuse me,
I'm looking for Maria Rambeau.

57:27.189 --> 57:28.756
Auntie Carol?

57:28.758 --> 57:30.693
Mom, it's Auntie Carol!

57:31.861 --> 57:34.595
I knew it!
Everyone said you were dead!

57:34.597 --> 57:36.666
But we knew they were lying.

57:38.768 --> 57:40.870
I'm not really
who you think I am.

57:50.046 --> 57:52.146
That is the craziest shit
I ever heard.

57:52.148 --> 57:55.282
Green transforming aliens?
There's no such thing.

57:55.284 --> 57:56.984
You are
absolutely right, young lady.

57:56.986 --> 57:58.719
There is no such thing.

57:58.721 --> 58:00.087
'Cause if there were,

58:00.089 --> 58:02.790
we would want to keep that
to ourselves.

58:02.792 --> 58:03.859
You don't believe me?

58:11.867 --> 58:13.600
No way!

58:13.602 --> 58:15.669
That's so cool!

58:15.671 --> 58:17.104
Oh, she can do
a lot more than make tea

58:17.106 --> 58:18.539
with those hands.

58:18.541 --> 58:19.640
Like what? Show us.

58:19.642 --> 58:20.943
Maybe later.

58:22.144 --> 58:23.677
I kept all your stuff.

58:23.679 --> 58:25.813
I'll go get it.

58:25.815 --> 58:27.483
You want to give her
a hand with that?

58:27.717 --> 58:28.784
Hmm?

58:43.799 --> 58:45.735
You don't remember anything?

58:47.103 --> 58:50.539
I see flashes.

58:51.674 --> 58:52.975
Little moments.

58:53.976 --> 58:55.578
But I can't tell
what's real.

58:57.813 --> 59:01.682
If I could just piece together
what happened that morning...

59:01.684 --> 59:03.919
maybe it'll all
make sense.

59:06.622 --> 59:10.325
You woke me up
banging on my door at dawn.

59:10.327 --> 59:12.760
Your usual move.

59:12.762 --> 59:15.696
Back then,
we had to get up so early.

59:15.698 --> 59:18.232
The Air Force still wasn't
letting women fly combat...

59:18.234 --> 59:20.934
so testing Lawson's planes
was our only shot

59:20.936 --> 59:22.236
at doing something
that mattered.

59:22.238 --> 59:25.139
You wanted to race to base
in your old Mustang...

59:25.141 --> 59:26.073
and I wasn't about to argue,

59:26.075 --> 59:28.175
'cause I knew
my Camaro would dominate.

59:28.177 --> 59:30.611
But you cheated,
took a shortcut.

59:30.613 --> 59:32.179
Since when is
a shortcut cheating?

59:32.181 --> 59:33.280
Since it violates
the predetermined

59:33.282 --> 59:34.382
rules of engagement.

59:34.384 --> 59:35.849
I definitely
don't remember those.

59:35.851 --> 59:37.651
Hmm. Of course you don't.

59:42.291 --> 59:47.861
When I got to the hangar,
Lawson was agitated.

59:47.863 --> 59:51.865
She said
she had lives to save.

59:51.867 --> 59:53.267
She was trying
to take the Asis up herself,

59:53.269 --> 59:54.402
but you said that...

59:54.404 --> 59:58.205
If there were lives at stake,
I would fly the plane.

59:58.207 --> 01:00:03.077
Yeah. Yep.
Big hero moment.

01:00:03.079 --> 01:00:07.014
The kind of moment
we'd both been waiting for.

01:00:07.016 --> 01:00:10.818
The doc was always unique.
That's why we liked her.

01:00:10.820 --> 01:00:15.358
But now you're saying
she's from another planet.

01:00:17.159 --> 01:00:18.892
I know this must be
hard for you.

01:00:18.894 --> 01:00:20.830
Oh, what?
This part right here?

01:00:21.664 --> 01:00:23.966
No. No. Mmm-mmm.

01:00:26.769 --> 01:00:31.205
Oh, what's hard
is losing my best friend...

01:00:31.207 --> 01:00:32.739
in a mission so secret

01:00:32.741 --> 01:00:34.810
they act like it never
even happened.

01:00:36.912 --> 01:00:40.348
Hard is knowing
you were out there somewhere

01:00:40.350 --> 01:00:42.251
too damn stubborn to die.

01:00:43.719 --> 01:00:46.454
And now you come up in here
after six years...

01:00:46.456 --> 01:00:48.689
with your supercharged
fire hands...

01:00:48.691 --> 01:00:50.791
and you expect me
to call you...

01:00:50.793 --> 01:00:52.329
I don't even know what.
Vers?

01:00:54.130 --> 01:00:56.098
Is that really
who you are now?

01:00:58.401 --> 01:01:00.136
I don't know.

01:01:05.207 --> 01:01:06.842
Come look!

01:01:13.182 --> 01:01:14.982
This is me and you
on Halloween.

01:01:14.984 --> 01:01:18.353
I'm Amelia Earhart
and you're Janis Joplin.

01:01:18.355 --> 01:01:20.087
Oh, this is you
when you were little.

01:01:20.089 --> 01:01:22.055
You didn't get along
with your parents...

01:01:22.057 --> 01:01:23.824
so Mom said
we became your real family.

01:01:23.826 --> 01:01:25.393
This is us on Christmas.

01:01:25.395 --> 01:01:26.528
I got my favorite
bunny slippers.

01:01:26.530 --> 01:01:28.463
This is another picture of you
when you were little.

01:01:28.465 --> 01:01:29.796
You've always wanted
to be a pilot.

01:01:29.798 --> 01:01:30.864
And this is right after
you graduated.

01:01:30.866 --> 01:01:32.099
This was your dog
that you got for Christmas...

01:01:32.101 --> 01:01:34.335
This is a picture of everybody
from your Air Force team.

01:01:34.337 --> 01:01:35.736
And this is you with Mom

01:01:35.738 --> 01:01:37.004
right after a good day
of training.

01:01:37.006 --> 01:01:38.306
These were
your three favorite guys.

01:01:40.743 --> 01:01:42.042
Oh, wait. I forgot.

01:01:42.044 --> 01:01:43.744
Your jacket.

01:01:43.746 --> 01:01:45.078
Mom doesn't
let me wear it anymore

01:01:45.080 --> 01:01:46.782
after I spilled
ketchup on it.

01:02:00.196 --> 01:02:02.298
That was all
that survived the crash.

01:02:03.533 --> 01:02:05.267
Or so we thought.

01:02:09.872 --> 01:02:11.905
Don't answer that.

01:02:11.907 --> 01:02:13.541
It's just my neighbor.

01:02:13.543 --> 01:02:15.277
They can change into anyone.

01:02:20.550 --> 01:02:22.049
Hi there.

01:02:22.051 --> 01:02:23.052
What do you want?

01:02:24.421 --> 01:02:26.220
- Uh...
- Hey, Tom.

01:02:26.222 --> 01:02:27.888
This is my friend, Carol.

01:02:27.890 --> 01:02:29.191
Oh. Pleased to meet you.

01:02:31.260 --> 01:02:32.560
Yowzers.

01:02:32.562 --> 01:02:35.796
Static electricity
out here's no joke.

01:02:35.798 --> 01:02:38.499
I noticed that peculiar bird
you got parked by the road...

01:02:38.501 --> 01:02:39.833
and I was just wondering...

01:02:39.835 --> 01:02:41.001
if you mind
if I bring the boys over

01:02:41.003 --> 01:02:42.202
to get a closer look-see?

01:02:42.204 --> 01:02:44.539
- A closer look-see?
- Yeah.

01:02:44.541 --> 01:02:47.843
To see the "bird"
parked out by the road?

01:02:48.110 --> 01:02:49.176
Mmm.

01:02:49.178 --> 01:02:50.811
You're really working
overtime

01:02:50.813 --> 01:02:54.181
to sell this one,
aren't you, Talos?

01:02:54.183 --> 01:02:56.984
I'm sorry, Tom.
This really isn't a good time.

01:02:56.986 --> 01:02:58.586
I'll come by tomorrow, okay?

01:02:58.588 --> 01:03:00.490
- Uh...
- Okay.

01:03:02.891 --> 01:03:06.827
You know, you really should be
kinder to your neighbors.

01:03:06.829 --> 01:03:08.061
You never know
when you're gonna need

01:03:08.063 --> 01:03:09.765
to borrow some sugar.

01:03:12.402 --> 01:03:14.602
Now, hang on a second.

01:03:14.604 --> 01:03:18.306
Before you go swinging
those jazz hands around...

01:03:18.308 --> 01:03:21.277
making a mess
of your friend's house...

01:03:22.077 --> 01:03:23.478
It's a lovely home, miss.

01:03:23.480 --> 01:03:24.780
Oh, my God!

01:03:25.214 --> 01:03:27.147
What the hell?

01:03:30.453 --> 01:03:32.021
No one's gonna hurt the girl.

01:03:32.555 --> 01:03:35.188
Just don't kill me.

01:03:35.190 --> 01:03:37.157
That would really complicate
the situation.

01:03:37.159 --> 01:03:39.960
I'm about five seconds
from complicating that wall

01:03:39.962 --> 01:03:41.329
with some ugly-ass
Skrull brains.

01:03:41.331 --> 01:03:43.096
I'm sorry
I simmed your boss.

01:03:43.098 --> 01:03:46.867
But now I stand before you
as my true self.

01:03:46.869 --> 01:03:48.135
Without deception.

01:03:48.137 --> 01:03:49.339
And who is that out there?

01:03:50.239 --> 01:03:52.873
Okay, that's a fair point...

01:03:52.875 --> 01:03:54.475
but I'm sure
that you understand

01:03:54.477 --> 01:03:56.910
I had to take
some precautions.

01:03:56.912 --> 01:04:00.113
I saw you crush
20 of my best men

01:04:00.115 --> 01:04:01.281
with your hands bound.

01:04:01.283 --> 01:04:02.517
I just wanna talk.

01:04:02.519 --> 01:04:03.584
Last time we talked,

01:04:03.586 --> 01:04:05.018
I ended up
hanging from my ankles.

01:04:05.020 --> 01:04:07.522
That was before I knew
who you were.

01:04:07.524 --> 01:04:10.826
Before I knew what made you
different from the others.

01:04:11.894 --> 01:04:14.094
I have an audio recording
from Pegasus...

01:04:14.096 --> 01:04:17.130
of your voice
from a plane crash

01:04:17.132 --> 01:04:18.599
six years ago...

01:04:18.601 --> 01:04:23.404
on a device I believe
you call a "black box."

01:04:23.406 --> 01:04:26.139
They told me it was
destroyed in the crash.

01:04:26.141 --> 01:04:27.342
How'd you get it?

01:04:27.344 --> 01:04:28.509
She don't understand.

01:04:28.511 --> 01:04:30.043
Young lady,
I have a special skill...

01:04:30.045 --> 01:04:31.479
that kind of allows me

01:04:31.481 --> 01:04:33.648
to get into places
I'm not supposed to be.

01:04:33.650 --> 01:04:35.015
Call me
"young lady" again...

01:04:35.017 --> 01:04:36.317
I'm gonna put my foot
in a place

01:04:36.319 --> 01:04:37.853
it's not supposed to be.

01:04:39.922 --> 01:04:42.191
Am I supposed to guess
where that is?

01:04:42.659 --> 01:04:43.725
Your ass.

01:04:43.727 --> 01:04:46.627
Okay, I get it. We're all
a little on edge here.

01:04:46.629 --> 01:04:48.596
But, look,
I just need your help

01:04:48.598 --> 01:04:50.097
decoding some coordinates.

01:04:50.099 --> 01:04:52.099
If you'll sit down
and you'll listen to this...

01:04:52.101 --> 01:04:55.237
I assure you,
it'll be worth your while.

01:04:58.006 --> 01:05:00.175
Call your buddy back inside
and I'll listen.

01:05:00.677 --> 01:05:01.942
Deal.

01:05:03.045 --> 01:05:05.078
Oh, my God!
Get that thing away.

01:05:05.080 --> 01:05:06.414
How'd that get in here?

01:05:06.416 --> 01:05:07.517
Hmm?

01:05:09.017 --> 01:05:10.117
The cat?

01:05:10.119 --> 01:05:11.619
This isn't what
you're afraid of, is it?

01:05:11.621 --> 01:05:12.921
That's not a cat.

01:05:13.956 --> 01:05:16.123
- That's a Flerken.
- A Flerken?

01:05:16.125 --> 01:05:17.627
Mom?

01:05:25.234 --> 01:05:26.367
Monica.

01:05:26.369 --> 01:05:28.003
- Why can't I listen, too?
- Shh!

01:05:55.665 --> 01:05:57.331
What's happening?

01:05:57.333 --> 01:05:58.635
It's loading.

01:06:02.672 --> 01:06:04.171
<i>Punch in the coordinates</i>

01:06:04.173 --> 01:06:08.609
<i>5-2-2-9,
negative 4-7, 8.7-6-8, 0.2.</i>

01:06:08.611 --> 01:06:10.711
<i>Copy that.
Where are we going, Doc?</i>

01:06:10.713 --> 01:06:12.346
<i>My laboratory.</i>

01:06:12.348 --> 01:06:14.649
<i>Your laboratory?
What do you mean?</i>

01:06:14.651 --> 01:06:15.683
<i>Oh, no.</i>

01:06:15.685 --> 01:06:18.151
<i>Is that...
Wait, what is that?</i>

01:06:18.153 --> 01:06:19.620
<i>It's not showing up
on my radar.</i>

01:06:19.622 --> 01:06:21.522
<i>Go, Carol. Fly!</i>

01:06:21.524 --> 01:06:24.057
That's no MiG, Lawson.
Who the hell are they?

01:06:24.059 --> 01:06:26.126
Those are the bad guys.
Fly faster now!

01:06:26.128 --> 01:06:27.129
Yes, ma'am.

01:06:33.235 --> 01:06:35.470
- What do they want?
- Me. My work.

01:06:35.472 --> 01:06:37.072
I never should have
brought you along.

01:06:42.244 --> 01:06:43.245
Here come some G's.

01:07:02.699 --> 01:07:04.467
They're firing backwards.
Hold on!

01:07:15.812 --> 01:07:17.212
Bail out! Bail out! Bail out!

01:07:21.149 --> 01:07:22.251
Stay with me, Lawson!

01:07:40.470 --> 01:07:41.869
<i>Carol, come in. Do you copy?</i>

01:07:41.871 --> 01:07:44.539
Yeah, I copy.
We hit ground.

01:07:44.541 --> 01:07:46.307
<i>Carol, are you okay?
Do you copy?</i>

01:07:46.309 --> 01:07:48.444
Yeah! I copy.

01:07:51.246 --> 01:07:52.247
Doc?

01:07:53.248 --> 01:07:54.617
Your blood.

01:07:55.451 --> 01:07:57.351
It's blue.

01:07:57.353 --> 01:08:00.490
Yeah, but, uh,
how's my hair?

01:08:01.858 --> 01:08:04.360
Help me out, will ya?

01:08:07.397 --> 01:08:10.565
I gotta destroy it
before they get here.

01:08:10.567 --> 01:08:12.165
Lawson?

01:08:12.167 --> 01:08:14.669
You remember what I said about
our work here?

01:08:14.671 --> 01:08:15.772
What it's for?

01:08:16.806 --> 01:08:18.306
To end wars?

01:08:18.308 --> 01:08:21.811
Yeah. But the wars are bigger
than you know.

01:08:23.178 --> 01:08:24.547
Damn it!

01:08:25.247 --> 01:08:27.582
My name is not Lawson.

01:08:27.584 --> 01:08:30.685
My real name is Mar-Vell,

01:08:30.687 --> 01:08:33.621
and I come
from a planet called Hala.

01:08:34.791 --> 01:08:37.190
I would say
that you're delusional...

01:08:37.192 --> 01:08:38.726
but we just got shot down
by a spaceship

01:08:38.728 --> 01:08:41.227
and your blood is blue.

01:08:41.229 --> 01:08:45.231
Listen, I spent half my life
fighting a shameful war.

01:08:45.233 --> 01:08:47.167
Now, skedaddle
before you give me

01:08:47.169 --> 01:08:48.469
any more regrets.

01:08:48.471 --> 01:08:51.204
Just remember
the coordinates, okay?

01:08:51.206 --> 01:08:52.807
You gotta save 'em without me.

01:08:52.809 --> 01:08:53.808
Save who? How?

01:08:53.810 --> 01:08:57.210
Now I gotta blow this engine
before they find it.

01:08:57.212 --> 01:08:58.448
What are you doing?

01:09:18.401 --> 01:09:20.470
We have no interest
in hurting you.

01:09:20.770 --> 01:09:22.036
No?

01:09:22.038 --> 01:09:24.907
'Cause all the shooting kinda
gave me the wrong impression!

01:09:26.542 --> 01:09:27.910
The energy core.

01:09:28.778 --> 01:09:30.311
Where is it?

01:09:30.313 --> 01:09:32.747
Pararescue's on the way.

01:09:32.749 --> 01:09:34.915
You have two minutes
until you're surrounded.

01:09:34.917 --> 01:09:37.752
Then I see no reason
to prolong this conversation.

01:09:37.754 --> 01:09:38.788
No, wait!

01:09:45.328 --> 01:09:46.629
You mean that energy core?

01:09:51.266 --> 01:09:52.368
No!

01:10:35.878 --> 01:10:39.513
Commander? She's still moving.
Permission to fire.

01:10:39.515 --> 01:10:40.516
Hold your fire.

01:10:50.526 --> 01:10:52.560
There's nothing left.

01:10:52.562 --> 01:10:54.296
The core has been destroyed.

01:11:03.773 --> 01:11:05.775
She absorbed its power.

01:11:07.977 --> 01:11:09.812
She's coming with us.

01:11:30.700 --> 01:11:32.001
He lied to me.

01:11:34.704 --> 01:11:36.804
Everything that I knew
was a lie.

01:11:36.806 --> 01:11:39.540
Now, you understand.

01:11:39.542 --> 01:11:42.076
What?
What do I understand now?

01:11:42.078 --> 01:11:44.111
Yon-Rogg killed Mar-Vell.

01:11:44.113 --> 01:11:45.414
He killed her...

01:11:46.115 --> 01:11:48.015
'cause she found out
that she was

01:11:48.017 --> 01:11:51.452
on the wrong side
of an unjust war.

01:11:51.454 --> 01:11:52.953
No.

01:11:52.955 --> 01:11:55.389
Your people are terrorists.

01:11:55.391 --> 01:11:56.924
They kill innocents.

01:11:56.926 --> 01:11:58.859
I saw the ruins on Torfa.

01:11:58.861 --> 01:12:02.563
Ruins that the Accusers
are responsible for.

01:12:02.565 --> 01:12:06.634
My people lived as refugees
on Torfa.

01:12:06.636 --> 01:12:09.737
Homeless, ever since
we resisted Kree rule...

01:12:09.739 --> 01:12:11.872
and they destroyed
our planet.

01:12:11.874 --> 01:12:15.609
And the handful of us
that are left

01:12:15.611 --> 01:12:17.778
will be slaughtered next...

01:12:17.780 --> 01:12:21.784
unless you help me finish
what Mar-Vell started.

01:12:23.019 --> 01:12:24.618
The core that she found

01:12:24.620 --> 01:12:26.387
would have powered
a light-speed ship...

01:12:26.389 --> 01:12:28.155
capable of carrying us
to safety.

01:12:28.157 --> 01:12:32.328
A new home where
the Kree can't reach us.

01:12:33.729 --> 01:12:36.063
Lawson always told us
that our work at Pegasus

01:12:36.065 --> 01:12:37.598
wasn't to fight wars...

01:12:37.600 --> 01:12:39.099
but to end them.

01:12:39.101 --> 01:12:44.740
She wanted you to help us
find the core.

01:12:45.708 --> 01:12:46.907
Well, I already destroyed it.

01:12:46.909 --> 01:12:48.676
No, you destroyed
the engine.

01:12:48.678 --> 01:12:51.812
The core that powered it
is in a remote location.

01:12:51.814 --> 01:12:56.183
If you help us
decode those coordinates...

01:12:56.185 --> 01:12:57.820
we can find it.

01:12:59.655 --> 01:13:01.357
You'll use it
to destroy us.

01:13:03.593 --> 01:13:06.562
We just want a home.

01:13:10.766 --> 01:13:16.070
You and I lost everything
at the hands of the Kree.

01:13:16.072 --> 01:13:18.072
Can't you see it now?

01:13:18.074 --> 01:13:19.575
You're not one of them.

01:13:22.612 --> 01:13:24.013
You don't know me.

01:13:25.514 --> 01:13:27.884
You have no idea
who I am.

01:13:29.986 --> 01:13:32.388
I don't even know
who I am!

01:13:33.623 --> 01:13:35.858
You are Carol Danvers.

01:13:37.059 --> 01:13:39.226
You are the woman
on that black box

01:13:39.228 --> 01:13:41.864
risking her life
to do the right thing.

01:13:43.699 --> 01:13:45.633
My best friend...

01:13:45.635 --> 01:13:48.636
who supported me
as a mother and a pilot

01:13:48.638 --> 01:13:50.704
when no one else did.

01:13:50.706 --> 01:13:55.910
You are smart, and funny,
and a huge pain in the ass...

01:13:55.912 --> 01:13:59.246
and you were the most
powerful person I knew...

01:13:59.248 --> 01:14:02.518
way before you could
shoot fire from your fists.

01:14:03.119 --> 01:14:04.654
You hear me?

01:14:05.988 --> 01:14:07.823
Do you hear me?

01:14:15.031 --> 01:14:17.033
Come here. Come here, girl.

01:14:17.767 --> 01:14:19.101
I got you.

01:14:23.506 --> 01:14:26.707
<i>I know
I don't deserve your trust...</i>

01:14:26.709 --> 01:14:28.943
but you were our only lead.

01:14:28.945 --> 01:14:31.211
We discovered
that your energy signature

01:14:31.213 --> 01:14:34.016
matched Mar-Vell's core.

01:14:34.884 --> 01:14:36.752
Now we know why.

01:14:38.621 --> 01:14:42.591
If only you knew
the importance of it to me.

01:14:43.693 --> 01:14:45.526
I just need your help

01:14:45.528 --> 01:14:49.730
decoding the coordinates
to Mar-Vell's lab.

01:14:49.732 --> 01:14:52.900
Those weren't coordinates.
They're state vectors.

01:14:52.902 --> 01:14:54.969
For orbital position
and velocity.

01:14:54.971 --> 01:14:56.804
You didn't find her lab
on Earth,

01:14:56.806 --> 01:14:58.138
'cause it's not on Earth.

01:14:58.140 --> 01:14:59.073
That was the location

01:14:59.075 --> 01:15:00.674
on the date
of the crash six years ago.

01:15:00.676 --> 01:15:02.042
If we track its course,

01:15:02.044 --> 01:15:04.611
we'll find it in orbit
right now.

01:15:04.613 --> 01:15:06.182
It's just basic physics.

01:15:08.751 --> 01:15:09.552
In orbit?

01:15:11.687 --> 01:15:13.287
Was that so difficult
to figure out?

01:15:13.289 --> 01:15:16.223
I mean, you're
my science guy, right?

01:15:16.225 --> 01:15:18.959
Yon-Rogg will catch up
to me soon.

01:15:18.961 --> 01:15:21.795
We've got to get to the core
before he does.

01:15:21.797 --> 01:15:23.664
Mmm. We're going
to space?

01:15:23.666 --> 01:15:24.732
In what?

01:15:24.734 --> 01:15:26.633
A few tweaks
to your vessel should do it.

01:15:26.635 --> 01:15:28.869
I can handle
the modifications.

01:15:28.871 --> 01:15:30.606
Mmm. Your science guy.

01:15:37.347 --> 01:15:38.981
Well, I could use
a copilot.

01:15:40.249 --> 01:15:42.916
No. No, I can't.

01:15:42.918 --> 01:15:44.952
I can't leave Monica.

01:15:44.954 --> 01:15:48.255
Mom, it's okay. I can stay
with Gramma and Paw-paw.

01:15:48.257 --> 01:15:50.624
There's no way I'm going,
baby. It's too dangerous.

01:15:50.626 --> 01:15:52.693
Testing brand-new aerospace
tech is dangerous...

01:15:52.695 --> 01:15:53.729
and you used to do that.

01:15:55.365 --> 01:15:57.332
Your plan
is to leave the atmosphere

01:15:57.334 --> 01:15:58.999
in a craft not designed
for the journey...

01:15:59.001 --> 01:16:00.834
and you anticipate
hostile encounters...

01:16:00.836 --> 01:16:01.935
with
a technologically-superior

01:16:01.937 --> 01:16:02.938
foreign enemy.

01:16:03.373 --> 01:16:04.938
Correct?

01:16:04.940 --> 01:16:06.006
That's what I'm saying.

01:16:06.008 --> 01:16:07.274
- You have to go!
- Monica!

01:16:07.276 --> 01:16:08.675
You have a chance
to fly the coolest mission

01:16:08.677 --> 01:16:09.910
in the history
of missions...

01:16:09.912 --> 01:16:11.779
and you're gonna give it up
to sit on the couch

01:16:11.781 --> 01:16:12.982
and watch <i>Fresh Prince</i>
with me?

01:16:13.783 --> 01:16:14.882
What?

01:16:14.884 --> 01:16:16.083
I just think
you should consider...

01:16:16.085 --> 01:16:19.322
what kind of example you're
setting for your daughter.

01:16:26.996 --> 01:16:28.396
What's going on around here?

01:16:28.398 --> 01:16:29.663
I know, I know.

01:16:29.665 --> 01:16:31.067
I'll explain inside.
Thank you.

01:16:36.072 --> 01:16:38.406
Your mom's lucky.

01:16:38.408 --> 01:16:39.907
When they were
handing out kids,

01:16:39.909 --> 01:16:42.109
they gave her
the toughest one.

01:16:42.111 --> 01:16:43.112
Lieutenant Trouble.

01:16:44.113 --> 01:16:45.748
You remembered.

01:16:47.116 --> 01:16:48.584
Is that mine?

01:16:49.285 --> 01:16:51.419
No, no.

01:16:51.421 --> 01:16:54.288
You hang on to it
until I come back.

01:16:54.290 --> 01:16:56.990
But there is something
that I need your help with.

01:16:56.992 --> 01:16:59.860
I can't wear
these Kree colors anymore.

01:16:59.862 --> 01:17:02.930
And since you are obviously
the only person around here

01:17:02.932 --> 01:17:04.800
with any sense of style...

01:17:06.035 --> 01:17:07.103
Hmm?

01:17:09.205 --> 01:17:10.239
Whoa.

01:17:12.875 --> 01:17:14.043
No.

01:17:16.313 --> 01:17:17.314
Uh-uh.

01:17:18.881 --> 01:17:20.415
Definitely not.

01:17:23.386 --> 01:17:25.821
Well, since we're
on the same team...

01:17:36.899 --> 01:17:38.033
Hmm.

01:17:39.336 --> 01:17:41.003
How do I look?

01:17:44.441 --> 01:17:45.875
Fresh.

01:18:05.794 --> 01:18:07.861
What took you so long?

01:18:07.863 --> 01:18:10.831
I'm fine.
Thanks for asking.

01:18:10.833 --> 01:18:13.267
- PRY46-B...
- No, no codes.

01:18:13.269 --> 01:18:15.037
That system is fallible,
as we've learned.

01:18:16.071 --> 01:18:18.406
Okay, then let's do this.

01:18:18.408 --> 01:18:21.875
Who do I see when I commune
with the Supreme Intelligence?

01:18:21.877 --> 01:18:24.778
The person you most admire
and respect, I'd guess.

01:18:24.780 --> 01:18:25.948
But you would never
tell me who.

01:18:27.384 --> 01:18:30.784
And what is your
earliest memory of Hala?

01:18:30.786 --> 01:18:32.320
The transfusion.

01:18:32.322 --> 01:18:34.522
Blue blood
running through my veins.

01:18:34.524 --> 01:18:35.724
Whose blood?

01:18:38.328 --> 01:18:39.362
Hmm.

01:18:46.835 --> 01:18:50.873
That's my blood that's
coursing through her veins.

01:18:55.412 --> 01:18:57.010
What have you done with her?

01:18:57.012 --> 01:18:58.981
You're too late.

01:19:15.465 --> 01:19:16.499
She knows?

01:19:31.247 --> 01:19:34.815
Ronan, Skrulls have
infiltrated C-53.

01:19:34.817 --> 01:19:35.949
Come at once.

01:19:35.951 --> 01:19:38.185
<i>For the good of all Kree,
Commander...</i>

01:19:38.187 --> 01:19:41.221
<i>the infestation
will be eradicated.</i>

01:19:43.158 --> 01:19:45.027
Passing 500 and climbing.

01:19:48.197 --> 01:19:51.466
You know, you really shouldn't
have that thing on your lap.

01:19:51.468 --> 01:19:54.935
Our little alliance with you
is tenuous at best.

01:19:54.937 --> 01:19:57.838
And as long as he continues
to freak you out...

01:19:57.840 --> 01:19:59.106
like that...

01:19:59.108 --> 01:20:01.509
yeah, I'm gonna keep
giving him

01:20:01.511 --> 01:20:04.512
all the loves and hugs
that he needs, right?

01:20:04.514 --> 01:20:06.314
Can I ask you something?

01:20:06.316 --> 01:20:08.516
Do you just turn into
anything you want?

01:20:08.518 --> 01:20:10.385
Ah, well,
I have to see it first.

01:20:10.387 --> 01:20:12.019
Can you all do it?

01:20:12.021 --> 01:20:13.954
Physiologically? Yeah.

01:20:13.956 --> 01:20:16.223
But, uh, it takes practice...

01:20:16.225 --> 01:20:20.160
and, um, dare I say it,
talent to do it well.

01:20:20.162 --> 01:20:22.863
- Can you turn into a cat?
- What's a cat?

01:20:22.865 --> 01:20:24.399
What about a filing cabinet?

01:20:24.401 --> 01:20:27.468
Why would I turn into
a filing cabinet?

01:20:27.470 --> 01:20:28.869
A Venus flytrap?

01:20:28.871 --> 01:20:29.936
I'll give you
50 bucks right now

01:20:29.938 --> 01:20:31.171
if you turn into
a Venus flytrap.

01:20:31.173 --> 01:20:32.973
Switching engines

01:20:32.975 --> 01:20:35.210
from Scramjet to Fusion.
Buckle up, folks.

01:20:44.354 --> 01:20:45.285
Hey.

01:20:45.287 --> 01:20:48.155
Is this normal,
like, space turbulence?

01:20:48.157 --> 01:20:49.158
Pretty much.

01:21:22.958 --> 01:21:24.960
Locking in
on coordinate grid.

01:21:25.428 --> 01:21:26.596
Where is it?

01:21:30.199 --> 01:21:33.133
It's here.
It's gotta be here.

01:21:33.135 --> 01:21:38.341
Well, is it in front of all
that nothing, or behind it?

01:21:43.979 --> 01:21:46.046
<i>Decloaking activated.</i>

01:22:49.044 --> 01:22:50.745
Is that it? The core?

01:22:50.747 --> 01:22:53.182
In her notes she called it
the Tesseract.

01:22:59.288 --> 01:23:00.356
Whoa.

01:23:02.024 --> 01:23:04.193
What was Lawson doing
with all this kid stuff?

01:23:18.140 --> 01:23:19.239
We're not alone.

01:23:42.297 --> 01:23:43.566
Talos!

01:23:53.510 --> 01:23:56.412
He didn't come here
for the Tesseract.

01:24:18.868 --> 01:24:20.235
It's okay.

01:24:25.207 --> 01:24:26.841
We didn't know what to do.

01:24:26.843 --> 01:24:30.411
Mar-Vell warned us not to send
a signal for any reason...

01:24:30.413 --> 01:24:32.178
or the Kree would find us.

01:24:32.180 --> 01:24:34.283
You did the right thing.

01:24:43.760 --> 01:24:45.593
It's okay, it's okay.

01:24:45.595 --> 01:24:47.664
She's all right.
She's a friend.

01:24:49.699 --> 01:24:51.632
I am not gonna hurt you.

01:24:51.634 --> 01:24:53.536
She led me to you.

01:24:54.337 --> 01:24:55.738
I'm so sorry.

01:24:57.507 --> 01:24:58.839
I didn't know.

01:24:58.841 --> 01:25:00.075
Carol.

01:25:00.743 --> 01:25:03.578
This is war.

01:25:03.580 --> 01:25:07.082
My hands are
filthy from it, too.

01:25:07.717 --> 01:25:09.850
But we're here now.

01:25:09.852 --> 01:25:13.088
You found my family.

01:25:15.925 --> 01:25:17.892
This is just the beginning.

01:25:17.894 --> 01:25:20.797
There are thousands of us
separated from each other...

01:25:21.898 --> 01:25:24.667
scattered throughout
the galaxy.

01:25:42.485 --> 01:25:44.785
If I played the same pinball
machine for six years...

01:25:44.787 --> 01:25:46.787
I'd have
some high scores, too.

01:25:49.425 --> 01:25:51.726
Fraternizing with the enemy?

01:25:51.728 --> 01:25:52.829
Uh-uh.

01:26:04.907 --> 01:26:07.207
What did you do
to your uniform?

01:26:07.209 --> 01:26:09.343
They got in her head.
Just like we thought.

01:26:09.345 --> 01:26:11.211
The Supreme Intelligence
will set her straight.

01:26:11.213 --> 01:26:12.680
You can see
they're not soldiers.

01:26:12.682 --> 01:26:15.248
Let 'em go.
You can have me.

01:26:15.250 --> 01:26:16.784
And the core?

01:26:16.786 --> 01:26:18.386
You lied to me.

01:26:18.388 --> 01:26:22.390
I made you
the best version of yourself.

01:26:25.695 --> 01:26:28.696
What's given
can be taken away.

01:26:42.512 --> 01:26:43.611
Back here! Move, move!

01:26:43.613 --> 01:26:46.181
Get over here. Get down!

01:26:46.683 --> 01:26:49.352
Let's go! Go, move!

01:27:28.691 --> 01:27:30.424
There she is.

01:27:30.426 --> 01:27:33.863
Seems like your time on C-53
jogged the old memory.

01:27:34.764 --> 01:27:36.630
This jacket.

01:27:36.632 --> 01:27:38.634
It's killer,
by the way.

01:27:40.036 --> 01:27:41.635
Oh.

01:27:41.637 --> 01:27:43.871
The music.
It's a nice touch.

01:27:43.873 --> 01:27:45.706
Let me out.

01:27:45.708 --> 01:27:47.641
No can do.

01:27:47.643 --> 01:27:51.545
If you hurt them,
I will burn you to the ground.

01:27:51.547 --> 01:27:53.481
With what exactly?

01:27:53.483 --> 01:27:54.882
Your power comes from us.

01:27:54.884 --> 01:27:56.817
You didn't give me
these powers.

01:27:56.819 --> 01:27:57.985
The blast did.

01:27:57.987 --> 01:27:59.453
And yet, you've never had
the strength

01:27:59.455 --> 01:28:00.556
to control them
on your own.

01:28:11.901 --> 01:28:13.667
<i>Species: Flerken.</i>

01:28:13.669 --> 01:28:15.669
<i>Threat: high.</i>

01:28:20.610 --> 01:28:22.512
It's a cat,
not Hannibal Lecter.

01:28:26.048 --> 01:28:27.748
<i>Species: human male.</i>

01:28:27.750 --> 01:28:29.952
<i>Threat: low to none.</i>

01:28:31.087 --> 01:28:32.653
That thing's
clearly busted.

01:28:32.655 --> 01:28:34.757
Load the Flerken
onto the <i>Helion.</i>

01:28:35.591 --> 01:28:37.560
Eject the others into space.

01:28:40.463 --> 01:28:42.498
You did good, Ace.

01:28:44.000 --> 01:28:45.132
Thanks to you...

01:28:45.134 --> 01:28:47.368
those insidious shapeshifters

01:28:47.370 --> 01:28:48.936
will threaten
our borders no more.

01:28:48.938 --> 01:28:51.472
I used to believe
your lies...

01:28:51.474 --> 01:28:54.108
but the Skrulls are
just fighting for a home.

01:28:54.110 --> 01:28:55.810
You're talking
about destroying them

01:28:55.812 --> 01:28:57.645
because they won't submit
to your rule.

01:28:57.647 --> 01:28:58.846
And neither will I.

01:28:58.848 --> 01:29:02.149
We found you.
We embraced you as our own.

01:29:02.151 --> 01:29:03.818
You stole me.

01:29:03.820 --> 01:29:06.654
From my home,
my family, my friends.

01:29:14.664 --> 01:29:16.566
It's cute how hard you try.

01:29:18.668 --> 01:29:20.403
But remember...

01:29:21.671 --> 01:29:22.970
without us...

01:29:22.972 --> 01:29:24.040
<i>Give it up, Carol.</i>

01:29:25.808 --> 01:29:27.107
<i>Stay down!</i>

01:29:27.109 --> 01:29:28.776
...you're weak.

01:29:28.778 --> 01:29:30.711
<i>You're going too fast!
You need to go slow!</i>

01:29:30.713 --> 01:29:32.112
You're flawed.

01:29:32.114 --> 01:29:33.482
<i>Are you trying
to kill yourself?</i>

01:29:34.450 --> 01:29:35.516
Helpless.

01:29:35.518 --> 01:29:36.584
<i>You're too emotional
and so weak.</i>

01:29:36.586 --> 01:29:38.986
<i>You don't belong out here!</i>

01:29:38.988 --> 01:29:40.688
We saved you.

01:29:40.690 --> 01:29:42.156
- <i>Control it.</i>
- <i>I told you,</i>

01:29:42.158 --> 01:29:43.224
- <i>Carol.</i>
- <i>They'll never</i>

01:29:43.226 --> 01:29:44.491
- <i>let you fly.</i>
- <i>This ain't</i>

01:29:44.493 --> 01:29:45.559
- <i>a game for little girls.</i>
- <i>You kiss like a horse.</i>

01:29:45.561 --> 01:29:46.729
<i>You won't last
a week, Danvers.</i>

01:29:49.799 --> 01:29:52.869
Without us,
you're only human.

01:29:54.437 --> 01:29:55.638
You're right.

01:29:56.839 --> 01:29:58.941
I'm only human.

01:30:32.909 --> 01:30:36.510
On Hala,
you were reborn...

01:30:36.512 --> 01:30:37.813
Vers.

01:30:42.818 --> 01:30:45.755
My name is Carol.

01:31:00.569 --> 01:31:02.038
She's trying to break out.

01:31:46.282 --> 01:31:49.752
I've been fighting with one
arm tied behind my back.

01:31:50.720 --> 01:31:52.252
But what happens when...

01:31:55.291 --> 01:31:57.526
I'm finally set free?

01:32:37.933 --> 01:32:40.701
You know you're glowing,
right?

01:32:40.703 --> 01:32:41.704
I'll explain it later.

01:32:44.273 --> 01:32:45.739
Take the Tesseract.

01:32:45.741 --> 01:32:46.974
Leave the lunchbox.

01:32:46.976 --> 01:32:48.709
- Me?
- Yes.

01:32:48.711 --> 01:32:50.110
I'm not touching that thing.

01:32:50.112 --> 01:32:51.180
You want me to
get you an oven mitt?

01:32:57.053 --> 01:32:58.220
Whoa!

01:33:04.927 --> 01:33:07.661
Get the Skrulls
on the Quadjet and go.

01:33:07.663 --> 01:33:10.331
Take the Flerken with you.

01:33:10.333 --> 01:33:12.101
- What about you?
- I'll buy you some time!

01:33:14.036 --> 01:33:15.905
I'm picking you up now.

01:33:19.008 --> 01:33:21.610
I'm trusting you
not to eat me.

01:33:26.782 --> 01:33:27.783
Oh, hey, guys.

01:33:31.687 --> 01:33:33.222
Arm wrestle
for the Tesseract?

01:33:36.326 --> 01:33:38.992
I used to find you amusing.

01:33:38.994 --> 01:33:39.995
Let's put an end to this.

01:34:15.365 --> 01:34:16.333
Okay.

01:34:16.899 --> 01:34:18.132
Good kitty.

01:35:04.481 --> 01:35:06.282
You knew all along.

01:35:07.384 --> 01:35:08.815
Is that why
we never hung out?

01:35:08.817 --> 01:35:09.919
No, I just never
liked you.

01:35:17.126 --> 01:35:18.127
Incoming!

01:35:26.536 --> 01:35:27.736
Hey, in a hurry?

01:35:29.939 --> 01:35:31.939
Don't make me do this.

01:35:31.941 --> 01:35:32.942
Okay.

01:35:48.824 --> 01:35:49.825
Come on, do your thing!

01:35:50.993 --> 01:35:52.061
Come on!

01:35:54.331 --> 01:35:55.929
Come on!

01:35:58.968 --> 01:36:00.335
Damn it, Goose.

01:36:00.337 --> 01:36:01.438
Pick a side.

01:36:05.808 --> 01:36:07.841
Take them
to the hangar, too.

01:36:07.843 --> 01:36:09.544
We'll blast them all
into space.

01:36:11.548 --> 01:36:12.748
Play it cool.

01:36:14.149 --> 01:36:15.418
Just like Havana.

01:36:17.253 --> 01:36:19.487
Do you have the thing?

01:36:19.489 --> 01:36:21.123
Flerken kitty ate it.

01:36:34.437 --> 01:36:36.069
Come on, move!

01:36:36.071 --> 01:36:37.206
Move!

01:36:37.873 --> 01:36:39.108
Follow my lead.

01:36:43.112 --> 01:36:44.113
Cover her eyes.

01:36:52.522 --> 01:36:54.288
Onto the ship!

01:36:54.290 --> 01:36:56.058
Let's go! Let's go!

01:37:18.947 --> 01:37:21.248
Nice diversion.

01:37:21.250 --> 01:37:23.052
I could have swore
I put it in there.

01:38:20.075 --> 01:38:22.275
Minn-Erva, take them down
in the drop ship.

01:38:22.277 --> 01:38:23.346
On it.

01:38:28.083 --> 01:38:29.184
You all right, friend?

01:38:30.252 --> 01:38:32.187
Never better.

01:38:37.025 --> 01:38:38.661
We got a bogey coming in hot.

01:40:18.595 --> 01:40:20.295
Yes! Boom!

01:40:36.312 --> 01:40:37.480
Whoo!

01:40:40.750 --> 01:40:42.217
What the hell was that?

01:41:05.542 --> 01:41:07.644
Deploy ballistic warheads.

01:41:59.862 --> 01:42:01.529
That's impossible.

01:42:01.531 --> 01:42:03.898
C-53 doesn't have
a defense system

01:42:03.900 --> 01:42:06.603
advanced enough
to destroy our warheads.

01:42:08.170 --> 01:42:10.573
That's not
their defense system, Ronan.

01:42:14.944 --> 01:42:16.278
Take her down.

01:42:36.231 --> 01:42:37.265
Whoo!

01:43:26.749 --> 01:43:28.685
Return to the jump point.

01:43:29.719 --> 01:43:31.821
We'll be back
for the weapon.

01:43:33.456 --> 01:43:34.624
The core?

01:43:36.492 --> 01:43:37.727
The woman.

01:44:25.842 --> 01:44:27.410
I'm so proud of you.

01:44:29.412 --> 01:44:30.778
You've come a long way

01:44:30.780 --> 01:44:33.380
since I found you
that day by the lake.

01:44:33.382 --> 01:44:35.549
But can you keep
your emotions in check

01:44:35.551 --> 01:44:37.852
long enough to take me on?

01:44:37.854 --> 01:44:40.590
Or will they get the
better of you as always?

01:44:42.024 --> 01:44:43.891
I always told you...

01:44:43.893 --> 01:44:45.392
you'll be ready

01:44:45.394 --> 01:44:47.795
the day you can knock
me down as yourself.

01:44:47.797 --> 01:44:49.497
This is that moment.

01:44:49.499 --> 01:44:52.032
This is that moment, Vers!

01:44:52.034 --> 01:44:53.434
Turn off the light show...

01:44:53.436 --> 01:44:56.706
and prove to me
you can beat me without...

01:45:12.121 --> 01:45:14.323
I have nothing
to prove to you.

01:45:30.006 --> 01:45:32.373
<i>Destination: Hala.</i>

01:45:32.375 --> 01:45:34.008
I can't go back empty-handed.

01:45:34.010 --> 01:45:35.943
You won't be empty-handed.

01:45:35.945 --> 01:45:38.512
I'm sending you
with a message.

01:45:38.514 --> 01:45:41.782
Tell the Supreme Intelligence
that I'm coming to end it.

01:45:41.784 --> 01:45:44.587
The war. The lies.
All of it.

01:45:46.489 --> 01:45:47.790
You can't do this.

01:46:06.709 --> 01:46:10.444
That was a close call,
huh, Goosey? Huh?

01:46:11.380 --> 01:46:12.880
Those bad guys
still in there somewhere?

01:46:12.882 --> 01:46:14.014
Ow!

01:46:14.016 --> 01:46:15.549
Mother Flerken!

01:46:15.551 --> 01:46:16.984
- You okay?
- Yeah.

01:46:16.986 --> 01:46:18.621
It's just a scratch.

01:46:18.921 --> 01:46:20.356
No.

01:46:27.797 --> 01:46:29.730
I can't believe

01:46:29.732 --> 01:46:31.131
you got in the raddest
dogfight ever...

01:46:31.133 --> 01:46:32.766
and I missed it.

01:46:32.768 --> 01:46:34.568
I'd say you arrived
just in time.

01:46:34.570 --> 01:46:36.737
Some nifty flying
you did out there.

01:46:36.739 --> 01:46:38.873
S.H.I.E.L.D. could always use
a good pilot like you.

01:46:38.875 --> 01:46:40.774
I'll consider it...

01:46:40.776 --> 01:46:43.911
as long as you never
call my flying "nifty" again.

01:46:43.913 --> 01:46:45.112
How's your eye?

01:46:45.114 --> 01:46:47.548
Hmm. Getting better
every second.

01:46:47.550 --> 01:46:48.849
Just so I'm clear...

01:46:48.851 --> 01:46:50.484
you were Soh-Larr...

01:46:50.486 --> 01:46:52.920
- and the S.H.I.E.L.D. agent?
- Keller.

01:46:52.922 --> 01:46:55.522
He tied my boss up,
stole his identity.

01:46:55.524 --> 01:46:58.525
I borrowed his likeness.
I'm no thief.

01:46:58.527 --> 01:46:59.860
It is a little like stealing.

01:46:59.862 --> 01:47:01.595
Whose side are you on here?

01:47:01.597 --> 01:47:03.097
You're good to go here
until you recover...

01:47:03.099 --> 01:47:06.467
but you and your family
are gonna need a new look.

01:47:06.469 --> 01:47:08.068
I could go back
to being your boss.

01:47:08.070 --> 01:47:09.169
Uh, please don't.

01:47:09.171 --> 01:47:12.206
Come on. I loved sporting
his beautiful blue eyes.

01:47:12.208 --> 01:47:14.842
No way.
You guys have the best eyes.

01:47:14.844 --> 01:47:16.877
Don't ever change
your eyes.

01:47:16.879 --> 01:47:18.512
She has beautiful eyes.
That's very sweet of you.

01:47:18.514 --> 01:47:20.180
I was trying
not to panic...

01:47:20.182 --> 01:47:21.751
I'll help you find a home.

01:47:22.818 --> 01:47:23.920
Finish what Mar-Vell started.

01:47:25.988 --> 01:47:28.489
They can stay here
with us.

01:47:28.491 --> 01:47:30.057
Can't they, Mom?

01:47:30.059 --> 01:47:32.693
They won't
be safe here, baby.

01:47:32.695 --> 01:47:34.261
Auntie Carol's right.

01:47:34.263 --> 01:47:35.464
They need their own home.

01:47:36.632 --> 01:47:38.832
I'll be back
before you know it.

01:47:38.834 --> 01:47:42.202
Or maybe I could fly up
and meet you halfway?

01:47:42.204 --> 01:47:45.172
Ah, only if you learn to glow
like your Auntie Carol.

01:47:45.174 --> 01:47:46.740
Or maybe I'll build
a spaceship.

01:47:46.742 --> 01:47:48.544
- You don't know.
- He doesn't.

01:47:58.154 --> 01:48:00.690
Keep the Tesseract
on Earth.

01:48:01.257 --> 01:48:02.589
Hidden.

01:48:02.591 --> 01:48:04.627
You sure that's what
Marvel would want?

01:48:05.161 --> 01:48:06.560
Mar-Vell.

01:48:06.562 --> 01:48:07.928
That's what I said.

01:48:07.930 --> 01:48:10.531
It's two words. Mar. Vell.

01:48:10.533 --> 01:48:11.932
Mar-Vell.

01:48:11.934 --> 01:48:13.067
"Marvel" sounds a lot better.

01:48:13.069 --> 01:48:14.503
You know,
like the Marvelettes.

01:48:28.250 --> 01:48:29.216
Not ringing any bells?

01:48:29.218 --> 01:48:31.253
Keep singing.
Maybe it'll come back to me.

01:48:46.736 --> 01:48:48.836
I upgraded it.

01:48:48.838 --> 01:48:51.207
Range should be a couple
galaxies, at least.

01:48:53.909 --> 01:48:56.210
What? You think
I'm gonna crank call you?

01:48:56.212 --> 01:48:59.849
For emergencies only, okay?

01:49:04.354 --> 01:49:07.221
Well...

01:49:07.223 --> 01:49:09.757
if you're ever passing
back through this galaxy...

01:49:09.759 --> 01:49:11.794
be sure to give
a brother a shout.

01:49:13.963 --> 01:49:15.831
Oh!

01:49:28.611 --> 01:49:30.646
We got
the ketchup stain off.

01:49:35.985 --> 01:49:37.820
Thanks,
Lieutenant Trouble.

01:49:39.822 --> 01:49:40.990
Hmm.

01:49:47.063 --> 01:49:49.797
It's hard for me
to say goodbye, too.

01:50:03.279 --> 01:50:04.613
Go on.

01:51:11.481 --> 01:51:14.283
Glad to have you back, sir.
This came for you.

01:51:19.221 --> 01:51:20.390
So, is it true?

01:51:21.458 --> 01:51:22.990
That the Kree
burned your eye out...

01:51:22.992 --> 01:51:26.260
because you refused
to give them the Tesseract?

01:51:26.262 --> 01:51:30.197
I will neither confirm nor
deny the facts of that story.

01:51:30.199 --> 01:51:31.267
Understood.

01:51:32.902 --> 01:51:33.867
I'm sorry to report

01:51:33.869 --> 01:51:35.102
that we still haven't
found the Tesseract.

01:51:35.104 --> 01:51:37.338
I'm sure it'll turn up
somewhere.

01:51:38.974 --> 01:51:40.874
I'll let you know
when it does.

01:51:40.876 --> 01:51:42.178
Then what?

01:51:42.811 --> 01:51:44.111
Sir?

01:51:44.113 --> 01:51:45.078
We have no idea

01:51:45.080 --> 01:51:48.449
what other intergalactic
threats are out there.

01:51:48.451 --> 01:51:50.518
And our one-woman
security force

01:51:50.520 --> 01:51:52.052
had a prior commitment...

01:51:52.054 --> 01:51:53.856
on the other side
of the universe.

01:51:56.526 --> 01:51:58.761
S.H.I.E.L.D. alone
can't protect us.

01:52:00.363 --> 01:52:02.229
We need to find more.

01:52:02.231 --> 01:52:03.364
More weapons?

01:52:03.366 --> 01:52:05.265
More heroes.

01:52:05.267 --> 01:52:06.967
You think you can find
others like her?

01:52:06.969 --> 01:52:09.972
Hmm, we found her,
and we weren't even looking.

01:52:11.040 --> 01:52:12.274
Get some rest, sir.

01:52:13.343 --> 01:52:15.211
You got
a big decision to make.

01:55:14.357 --> 01:55:16.091
This is a nightmare.

01:55:17.660 --> 01:55:20.028
I've had better nightmares.

01:55:22.164 --> 01:55:23.198
Hey.

01:55:24.266 --> 01:55:26.401
So, that thing just stopped

01:55:26.403 --> 01:55:28.170
doing whatever the hell
it was doing.

01:55:30.105 --> 01:55:32.673
What do we got?

01:55:32.675 --> 01:55:35.275
Whatever signal it was
sending finally crapped out.

01:55:35.277 --> 01:55:36.377
I thought
we bypassed the battery.

01:55:36.379 --> 01:55:37.512
We did.

01:55:37.514 --> 01:55:41.315
It's still plugged in.
It just stopped.

01:55:41.317 --> 01:55:43.250
Reboot it.
Send the signal again.

01:55:43.252 --> 01:55:44.719
We don't even know
what this is.

01:55:44.721 --> 01:55:47.455
Fury did.
Just do it, please.

01:55:47.457 --> 01:55:50.190
You tell me
the second you get a signal.

01:55:50.192 --> 01:55:52.595
I wanna know who's on
the other end of that thing.

01:55:55.532 --> 01:55:57.065
Where's Fury?
